1. There was a regional anesthesia procedure.
2. There were different groups in the procedure, including an epidural group.
3. The procedure time for regional anesthesia was measured.
4. The procedure time was longer in the epidural group.
5. The difference in procedure time between the epidural group and others was statistically significant.
6. The P-value for the difference in procedure time was less than 0.001.

messages.content:
Statement: Regional anesthesia procedure time was significantly longer in the epidural group (P < 0.001).
